'''Comprehend Speech''' or '''Language Absorption'''<ref>''[[Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide]]''</ref> was a [[The Force/Legends|Force]] [[Force power/Legends|ability]] that enabled a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] or [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] to understand the spoken [[Language/Legends|language]] of any sentient they were interacting with, though it does not necessarily allow them to speak it, merely understand the general meaning. It is possibly an extension of the [[Telepathy/Legends|Telepathy]] power, as [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] was described as "ripping the [[Rakata (language)|Rakatan]] language from their minds," comprehending their tongue only moments after meeting them. [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] also demonstrated this ability on [[Nelvaan/Legends|Nelvaan]], having been able to understand and translate the speech of a [[Nelvaanian/Legends|Nelvaanian]] [[Shaman/Legends|shaman]] [[Orvos]], though some of the nuances of the speech evaded him. This power proved ineffective at comprehending the language of extremely xenophobic cultures, as evidenced by Revan's inability to understand the [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Sand People]] [[Tusken|dialect]]. It can be guessed that cultures that actively refuse contact with other cultures, such as not caring whether a particular individual can communicate with them or not, can negate this ability. Use of the ability was aided if the sentient itself was [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] to some degree, as demonstrated when [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] encountered the [[Qom Jha and Qom Qae|Qom Jha]] on [[Nirauan/Legends|Nirauan]] and found he understood their language without making an attempt to interpret it.

This power was known to the [[Witches of Dathomir]] as the [[Spell of Interpretation]].

Mace Windu used this ability to understand [[Kar Vastor]]'s guttural language.<ref name="Shatterpoint (novel)">[[Shatterpoint (novel)|''Shatterpoint'']]</ref>

